commentPostTextItems.html: Join us for the next game. Cheers

Thilan Samaraweera, Man of the Match "It was easy to bat because of the dew. I knew we needed a partnership, myself and Kumar did well. In the end, Perera did really well. The ball is coming onto the bat really well because of the dew."

Kumar Sangakkara "All credit to Sammy for batting through, and Perera played superbly too. When we started out in the morning, it was like 'here we go again', but Welegedara did well to bring us back in. Suraj Randiv bowled well, and I think our fielding was much better. The attitude of the players was brilliant, we were out there to win." Bad news meanwhile, Sanga informs us that Pushpakumara is going back because of the shoulder injury

MS Dhoni "It was always going to be difficult to defend 280. We knew we had to pick early wickets, after the first 10 overs there was nothing for the bowlers. We can request to have an early start, but if you have to play at the same time, you have to come up with something else. It's just slipping out, no yorkers, no reverse-swing, no spin."

For those who didn't watch this one live, we hope you enjoyed our text commentary. Samaraweera played a superb middle-order knock, 105 off 106, never looking hurried, and Perera ran away with it in the end when Sri Lanka were threatening to choke. India opened the bowling well, Nehra was special, and then the middle overs featured too many singles, and after the comeback fashioned by Harbhajan, their fast bowlers just couldn't stop Perera, bowling fulltosses, no-balls, leg-side half-volleys. Consequently, Sri Lanka lead the table. Stay with us for the presentation ceremony

commentPostTextItems.html: Dhoni asks for a ball change, which should suggest the previous fulltoss slipped out of Nehra's hand. Umpires say, no way Jose

commentTextItems.html: two balls, two fours for Perera, what a player, Nehra misses the yorker by inches and he goes inside-out and pierces the off-side field from outside leg
another slower ball, this time he stands his ground and works it towards fine leg for one
he makes room again, and Nehra follows him with a slower delivery and beats him
